In addition, the new species is distinguishable from all other congeners by the following morphological characteristics: (1) dactylus of major cheliped with a prominent bifid proximal tooth and a triangular notch on the opposable margin (
Fig. 3A, B
); (2) fixed finger of minor cheliped has long, sharp teeth, and an additional row of teeth on mesial surface (
Fig. 3C, D
); and (3) dactylus of pereopod 5 armed with one corneous spiniform seta on upper-mesial surface (
Fig. 4K
). In view of the above, a new species is warranted.
